models:
- name: prototype_similarity
  rationale: 'Random-looking sequences are close to a prototype with balanced H/T counts and an ideal alternation rate.'
- name: encoding_compressibility
  rationale: 'Random-looking sequences are those with low simple-description penalties: long runs, periodic templates, and imbalance.'
- name: inner_loop_model
  rationale: 'Best PyMC model found by the inner model-improvement loop.'
- name: inferred_mixture_model
  rationale: 'A variant of the Bayesian mixture model that infers the parameters of the alternative hypotheses (alternating Markov, streaky Markov, and biased coin) rather than keeping them hardcoded.'
- name: unnormalized_mixture_model
  rationale: 'A variant of the inner loop model that does not normalize log probabilities by sequence length, to test if length normalization was the critical success factor.'
